zornmesh service
Manage the per-user zornmesh daemon as a supervised background service.

Usage: zornmesh service <install|uninstall|status>

Subcommands:
      install     Write the launchd plist (macOS) or systemd user unit (Linux)
      uninstall   Remove the previously installed unit file
      status      Report install state and daemon reachability
  -h, --help     Print help

The install subcommand writes only the unit file. It prints the exact
activation command (launchctl bootstrap or systemctl --user enable) so
operators can audit the change before it takes effect. Running as root
is refused; the unit is per-user and points at the current binary.
